# DevOps

- **Environments**: `dev`, `staging`, `prod` with distinct secrets and API URLs; never commit secrets.
- **CI**: on PR—lint, typecheck, unit tests (web + **api-rust** + **api-node**); on main—build images or deploy per pipeline. For `web/`, `api-node/`, and `test/`: **Node.js 24.14.1**, **Corepack** + **pnpm** (`pnpm install --frozen-lockfile`).
- **Security**: follow the **security** rule (lockfile, audits, secrets, headers).
- **Containers**: multi-stage builds; run as non-root; pin base image digests where practical.
- **Compose resources**: `docker-compose.yml` uses five YAML anchors only — **`x-resources-tiny`** through **`x-resources-huge`** (`deploy.resources.limits`). Assign heavier work to **`big`** / **`huge`**; raise limits if local OOM or slow builds.
- **Compose DNS (egress control)**: Every workload on **`dev-internal`** merges anchor **`x-dns-filtered`** (`dns: [172.28.0.53]`) and **`depends_on: dns-filter`** (`service_started`). **`dns-filter`** (CoreDNS) is the exception—no custom **`dns`**, so it keeps Docker embedded DNS and avoids a resolver loop. When adding a service, extend **`local-env/network/Corefile`** **`compose_services`** **`name() in [...]`** so Docker internal names forward to **`127.0.0.11`**; add whitelist **`zonename:53`** blocks for new external zones as needed. **`notify`** (Compose profiles **`dev`**, **`test`**, **`deps`**, **`full`**): sidecar that **polls** **`dns-filter`** logs over **`docker.sock`** and runs **`notify-send`** via host session D-Bus. Set **`NOTIFY_DBUS`** to the host session socket (**`$XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/bus`**, often **`/run/user/$(id -u)/bus`**) and **`NOTIFY_DESKTOP_UID` / `NOTIFY_DESKTOP_GID`** to **`id -u` / `id -g`** so **`su-exec`** invokes **`notify-send`** as your desktop user (root in-container is rejected by the session bus). Bus bind is **writable** (not `:ro`). **`notify`** uses **`security_opt: apparmor=unconfined`** so Ubuntu’s default Docker **AppArmor** profile does not block **D-Bus** `Hello` on the mounted session bus (otherwise **`AccessDenied`** and **`notify-send`** falls back to stdout). SELinux hosts may need **`label:disable`** instead—adjust locally. **`notify`**: **first** **`NXDOMAIN`/`SERVFAIL`** → **immediate** intro toast (domain + compose service); **later** rows dedupe by **service + hostname** (**A**/**AAAA** merge) into a follow-up queue; after **`DNS_FILTER_NOTIFY_BATCH_SEC`** (default **5s** from the intro) sends **one toast per service** listing further domains; idle deadline with an empty follow-up queue resets state. **`DNS_FILTER_NOTIFY_TICK_SEC`** wakes the reader (default **1s**). **Global ceiling**: at most **`DNS_NOTIFY_GLOBAL_MAX`** toasts (default **10**) per rolling **`DNS_NOTIFY_GLOBAL_WINDOW_SEC`** (default **300**); the **first** block in an episode sends **one** extra cap-explanation toast (**not** counted); set max or window **≤0** to disable. **`DNS_NOTIFY_POLL_SEC`** / **`DNS_NOTIFY_SINCE_SEC`** tune log polling. **Caller labels**: CoreDNS **`log`** lines include the **querier IP**; **`notify`** maps it to **`com.docker.compose.service`** on **`NOTIFY_DOCKER_NETWORK`** (auto: `*_dev-internal` from the sidecar’s networks; override in compose). Cache TTL **`DNS_NOTIFY_IP_MAP_SEC`** (default **30**). **`depends_on`** **`notify`**. **Host log tail** (no toasts): `docker compose logs -f dns-filter`. Headless CI: log-only / no DBus is fine.
- **Dependency edits** (workflow detail: **`deps-compose-docker`** skill): Compose profile **`deps`** — services **`web-deps`**, **`api-node-deps`**, **`api-rust-deps`** build from **`Dockerfile.deps`** (repo-root context) and bind-mount **`./web`**, **`./api-node`**, **`./api-rust`** so manifests, lockfiles, **`node_modules`**, and **`target`** stay on the host. Entrypoints **`local-env/deps/*-entrypoint.sh`** whitelist `pnpm` / `cargo` verbs. Run **`just web-deps`**, **`just api-node-deps`**, **`just api-rust-deps`** (wrap `docker compose --profile deps run --rm --build --user …`).
- **App tests (Docker)**: Profile **`test`** — **`web-test`** (**`pnpm run typecheck`**, **`lint`**, **`test`**, **`test/smoke.test.ts`**), **`api-node-test`** (**`pnpm run test`**, **`test/smoke.test.ts`**, **`DATABASE_URL`** + **`OPENAI_*`**, **`storage-main`** / **`storage-migrate`**), **`api-rust-test`** (**`cargo test --test smoke`**, **`DATABASE_URL`** + **`REDIS_URL`** + **`OPENAI_*`**, **`storage-main`** / **`storage-migrate`** / **`storage-cache`**), **`storage-test`**. **`just test`** → the Compose `test` profile (static test images only).
- **pnpm store**: `web/.npmrc` and `api-node/.npmrc` use **`store-dir=../.pnpm-store`** (repo **`/.pnpm-store`**, gitignored). **`web-dev`**, **`api-node-dev`**, **`web-deps`**, and **`api-node-deps`** bind-mount **`./.pnpm-store`** → **`/.pnpm-store`**. **`local-env/deps/ensure-pnpm-store-writable.sh`** runs from **`just`** before those flows so the host dir is user-writable (fixes Docker-created root-owned dirs via a one-off **`alpine`** `chown`). **`web-deps`** / **`api-node-deps`** set **`CI=true`** so non-interactive **`pnpm install`** does not require a TTY for modules purge; **`local-env/deps/pnpm-entrypoint.sh`** runs **`add`** / **`remove`** / **`update`** with **`CI`** unset so **`pnpm-lock.yaml`** is always refreshed on the bind-mounted tree.
- **Database**: **PostgreSQL**; migrations run in CI/CD or a controlled job, not ad hoc on app boot in production. Backups and restore drills for prod.
